---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Jack Peng's resume and learning journey"
	pubDate={new Date()}
>
	<div class="prose max-w-none">
		<h1>Jack Peng</h1>
		<p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-8">
			SOFTWARE/AI ENGINEER • Redwood City, CA • <a href="mailto:jackpeng@gmail.com">jackpeng@gmail.com</a> • <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/jack-peng-5475b45/">LinkedIn</a>
		</p>

		<h2>The Journey: A Perpetual Student of the Stack</h2>
		<p>
			I’m a software explorer. My path hasn't been about following a predefined roadmap, but rather following the "scent" of interesting problems. I transitioned into software in my late 30s, and since then, I’ve found that the more I learn, the more I realize how much fun there is to be had in the layers I haven't touched yet.
		</p>

		<h3>Exploring the "How"</h3>
		<p>I didn't set out to become a systems engineer; I just started pulling on threads.</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>The Backend:</strong> I started with Go and Python, falling in love with the speed of building and the power of concurrency.</li>
			<li><strong>The Metal:</strong> That led me to Rust, where I traded "moving fast" for the satisfying precision of memory safety and ownership.</li>
			<li><strong>The Virtual:</strong> Recently, I've been deep in the world of Firecracker MicroVMs, learning how to hand-roll networking TAPs and bridge the gap between a web terminal and a Linux kernel.</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>What’s on the Horizon?</h3>
		<p>I’m currently in a "learning sprint," and my curiosity is pulling me in three exciting directions:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Agentic Patterns:</strong> Exploring the world of AI agents—not just as chatbots, but as autonomous systems that can reason and execute tasks.</li>
			<li><strong>The Frontend:</strong> I’ve spent a lot of time "under the hood," so now I’m turning my attention to the dashboard. I'm diving into modern frontend development (like this Astro blog!) to make the systems I build beautiful and intuitive.</li>
			<li><strong>Kubernetes (K8s):</strong> After building my own microVM orchestrator from scratch, I’m ready to see how the industry "pros" handle orchestration at a massive scale.</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Beyond the Code</h3>
		<p>When I'm not wrestling with Rust lifetimes or iptables rules, I’m probably:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>At the Piano:</strong> Learning the intricacies of a Mozart or Chopin piece.</li>
			<li><strong>On the Court:</strong> Playing basketball or table tennis (Ping Pong technique is a never-ending pursuit!).</li>
			<li><strong>In the Past:</strong> Reading American history or deep-diving into a historical biography.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>I'm having a blast exploring this vast landscape, and this blog is my way of documenting the "aha!" moments along the way.</p>

		<hr class="my-12 border-gray-200" />

		<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">My Learning Stack</h2>
		<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
			<!-- Go/Python Card -->
			<div class="relative group rounded-xl p-8 bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-2 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-blue-500/20 z-10 overflow-hidden">
				<div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50/0 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300 blur-xl"></div>
				<div class="relative z-20">
					<div class="text-4xl mb-4 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300 origin-bottom-left">🚀</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 m-0 mb-2">Go & Python</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed m-0">
						The backend foundations. Speed, concurrency, and rapid iteration. Where my software journey accelerated.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Rust/Firecracker Card -->
			<div class="relative group rounded-xl p-8 bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-2 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-orange-500/20 z-10 overflow-hidden">
				<div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-red-50/0 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300 blur-xl"></div>
				<div class="relative z-20">
					<div class="text-4xl mb-4 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300 origin-bottom-left">🦀</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 m-0 mb-2">Rust & Firecracker</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed m-0">
						Close to the metal. Memory safety, extreme performance, and custom microVM orchestration.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Agentic AI Card -->
			<div class="relative group rounded-xl p-8 bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-2 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-purple-500/20 z-10 overflow-hidden">
				<div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-fuchsia-50/0 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300 blur-xl"></div>
				<div class="relative z-20">
					<div class="text-4xl mb-4 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300 origin-bottom-left">🧠</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 m-0 mb-2">Agentic AI</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed m-0">
						The frontier. Exploring autonomous systems, reasoning boundaries, and LLM-driven architectures.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

